.\"
.\"
.SH BUGS
.PP
The
.IR AIX \(rg
compatibility suite has no known bugs.
.\"
.\"
.SH COMPATIBILITY
.PP
These functions are compatible with
.IR AIX \(rg
with the following portability considerations:
.IP \(em \w'\(em\(em'u
Neither
.IR AIX \(rg-specific,
nor
.IR MPS \(rg,
functions should be used by portable
.I STREAMS
drivers and modules.
The more common
.I SVR 4.2 MP
functions should be used in their stead.
.IP \(em
.IR AIX \(rg-specific
functions are provided for source level compatibility with
.IR AIX \(rg
for the purpose of porting
.IR AIX \(rg
drivers to
.BR Linux .
Because internal structures and definitions for
.B @PACKAGE_TITLE@
.[
lfs
.]
differ from that of
.IR AIX \(rg,
binaries are incompatible.
.IP \(em
.IR AIX \(rg-specific
functions only provide functionality comparable to
.IR AIX \(rg
for use by
.I STREAMS
drivers and modules.
Any and all functionality provided by
.IR AIX \(rg-specific
functions in support of
.RI non- STREAMS
devices are not supported.
.PP
See
.BR STREAMS (9)
for additional compatibility considerations.
.\"
.\"
.SH CONFORMANCE
.PP
.IR AIX \(rg
DDI documentation.
.[
aixdoc
.]
.[
aixspg
.]
.\"
.\"
